ANC stalwart, Cheryl Carolus spoke out against the article written by Tourism Minister Lindiwe Sisulu. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC stalwart Cheryl Carolus says Tourism Minister Lindiwe Sisulu must be fired. Carolus says Sisulu is way out of line. READ: SA Constitution | Zondo slams Sisulu's comments She was reacting to an opinion piece penned by Sisulu in which she questions what South Africa’s Constitution has done for apartheid victims, except as a palliative to relieve pain without dealing with the causes of the condition. Earlier, Acting Chief Justice Raymond Zondo also responded to Sisulu's article, saying it lacks facts and proper analysis.